  - STATE_UPDATE: {'generated_prompt': 'Now I need to use the content field from the return result as my final output. The prompt has been generated successfully.\n\nYou are a premier expert in software testing. Fix the build for: libstdcpp.\n\n--- 【EXPERT KNOWLEDGE & STRATEGIC GUIDANCE】 ---\nBased on the fuzz build log analysis:\n\n**BUILD FAILURE ANALYSIS:**\nThe build is failing at the fuzzer compilation/linking stage. The key issue is a compiler flag conflict:\n\n**PROBLEM IDENTIFIED:**\n1. **Compiler Flag Incompatibility**: The fuzzer compilation command uses `-stdlib=libc++` but then links against `libstdc++.a`. This creates a fundamental incompatibility between using libc++ headers and linking against libstdc++ library.\n\n2. **Conflicting Directives**:\n   - `-stdlib=libc++`: Instructs the compiler to use libc++ as the C++ standard library\n   - `-nostdinc++`: Prevents using standard C++ include paths\n   - `-cxx-isystem /out/install.d/include/c++/16.0.1/`: Uses libstdc++ headers\n   - Linking against `/out/install.d/lib64/libstdc++.a`: Links against libstdc++ library\n\n3. **Root Cause**: The build script is trying to mix libc++ and libstdc++ components, which are incompatible. When using `-stdlib=libc++`, the compiler expects to link against libc++ library, not libstdc++.\n\n**EXPERT RECOMMENDATIONS:**\n1. **Remove `-stdlib=libc++` flag**: Since the project is building and linking against libstdc++, the `-stdlib=libc++` flag should be removed from the fuzzer compilation command.\n\n2. **Check build.sh script**: The issue likely originates in the `build.sh` script where fuzzer compilation flags are set. Look for where `CXXFLAGS` or similar variables are defined with `-stdlib=libc++`.\n\n3. **OSS-Fuzz Environment Variables**: Check if environment variables like `CXXFLAGS` or `FUZZING_ENGINE` flags are incorrectly adding `-stdlib=libc++`.\n\n4. **Alternative Solution**: If libc++ is required for some reason, ensure consistent usage:\n   - Use `-stdlib=libc++` consistently\n   - Link against libc++ library instead of libstdc++\n   - Use libc++ headers instead of libstdc++ headers\n\n**PATTERN MATCHING:**\nThis is a common issue in OSS-Fuzz builds where the default fuzzing environment assumes libc++ for better sanitizer compatibility, but some projects (like libstdc++ itself) need to use their own standard library implementation.\n\n**IMMEDIATE ACTION:**\nExamine the `build.sh` script in the project configuration directory and remove or modify the `-stdlib=libc++` flag from the fuzzer compilation commands.\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 1] Significant progress: Successfully built and installed libstdc++ (original error was gcc compilation failure with struct/class mismatches). Now at fuzzer compilation stage. Environment locking and correct commit checkouts resolved the initial compilation issues.\n- [Attempt 2] Stagnant progress: Still failing at fuzzer compilation stage. The flag filtering fix removed -stdlib=libc++ but introduced duplicate flags issue. The sed command filtering may not be handling flags correctly, and -nostdinc++ with libstdc++ headers might still be problematic. Need a cleaner approach to compiler flag management.\n- [Attempt 1] Significant progress made! Original error was GCC compilation failure (make[1]: *** [Makefile:4764: all-gcc] Error 2). Current build successfully compiled and installed libstdc++ libraries, reaching the fuzzer linking stage. The core library build succeeded, only fuzzer linking remains. This represents excellent forward movement from compilation to linking stage.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2023 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:6d7dd44ebec7ae27386a7b8a37ce0e827fe1604c33ef5a3a009a10f0fdf7bc34\nRUN sed -i -e \'s/^# deb-src/deb-src/g\' /etc/apt/sources.list\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y make autoconf automake libtool\nRUN apt build-dep -y g++-10\nRUN git clone  git://gcc.gnu.org/git/gcc.git libstdcpp\nWORKDIR libstdcpp\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\nADD https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pauldreik/stdfuzz/main/format/one-arg.cpp $SRC/\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2023 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\nSRCDIR=$SRC/libstdcpp\nBUILDDIR=$OUT/build.d\nINSTALLDIR=$OUT/install.d\nmkdir -p $BUILDDIR $INSTALLDIR\n\n(\n    cd $BUILDDIR\n    CXX= CC= CXXFLAGS= CFLAGS= $SRCDIR/configure \\\n       --disable-bootstrap \\\n       --prefix=$INSTALLDIR \\\n       --enable-languages=c++\n    make -j$(nproc)\n    make -j$(nproc) install-target-libstdc++-v3\n)\n\nfor fuzzsrcfile in /src/*.cpp; do\n    targetfile=$(basename $fuzzsrcfile .cpp)\n    $CXX \\\n\t$CXXFLAGS \\\n\t-std=c++20 \\\n\t-nostdinc++ \\\n\t-cxx-isystem $( echo $INSTALLDIR/include/c++/*/ ) \\\n\t-cxx-isystem $( echo $INSTALLDIR/include/c++/*/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu ) \\\n\t$fuzzsrcfile \\\n\t-o $OUT/$targetfile \\\n\t$LIB_FUZZING_ENGINE \\\n\t$INSTALLDIR/lib64/libstdc++.a\ndone\n\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://gcc.gnu.org/"\nlanguage: c++\nprimary_contact: "pauldreikossfuzz@gmail.com"\nauto_ccs:\n - "jwakely.gcc@gmail.com"\nmain_repo: "git://gcc.gnu.org/git/gcc.git"\nfile_github_issue: false\narchitectures:\n - x86_64\nsanitizers:\n - address\n - undefined\nfuzzing_engines:\n  - libfuzzer\n  - afl\n  - honggfuzz\n# - centipede\n\n\n--- Project File Tree (Shallow View) ---\n📁 libstdcpp\n├── 📄 ABOUT-NLS\n├── 📄 COPYING\n├── 📄 COPYING.LIB\n├── 📄 COPYING.RUNTIME\n├── 📄 COPYING3\n├── 📄 COPYING3.LIB\n├── 📄 ChangeLog\n├── 📄 ChangeLog.jit\n├── 📄 ChangeLog.tree-ssa\n├── 📁 INSTALL\n├── 📄 MAINTAINERS\n├── 📄 Makefile.def\n├── 📄 Makefile.in\n├── 📄 Makefile.tpl\n├── 📄 README\n├── 📄 SECURITY.txt\n├── 📄 ar-lib\n├── 📁 c++tools\n├── 📄 compile\n├── 📁 config\n├── 📄 config-ml.in\n├── 📄 config.guess\n├── 📄 config.rpath\n├── 📄 config.sub\n├── 📄 configure\n├── 📄 configure.ac\n├── 📁 contrib\n├── 📄 depcomp\n├── 📁 fixincludes\n├── 📁 gcc\n├── 📁 gnattools\n├── 📁 gotools\n├── 📁 include\n├── 📄 install-sh\n├── 📁 libada\n├── 📁 libatomic\n├── 📁 libbacktrace\n├── 📁 libcc1\n├── 📁 libcody\n├── 📁 libcpp\n├── 📁 libdecnumber\n├── 📁 libffi\n├── 📁 libga68\n├── 📁 libgcc\n├── 📁 libgcobol\n├── 📁 libgfortran\n├── 📁 libgm2\n├── 📁 libgo\n├── 📁 libgomp\n├── 📁 libgrust\n├── 📁 libiberty\n├── 📁 libitm\n├── 📁 libobjc\n├── 📁 libphobos\n├── 📁 libquadmath\n├── 📁 libsanitizer\n├── 📁 libssp\n├── 📁 libstdc++-v3\n├── 📄 libtool-ldflags\n├── 📄 libtool.m4\n├── 📁 libvtv\n├── 📄 ltgcc.m4\n├── 📄 ltmain.sh\n├── 📁 lto-plugin\n├── 📄 ltoptions.m4\n├── 📄 ltsugar.m4\n├── 📄 ltversion.m4\n├── 📄 lt~obsolete.m4\n├── 📁 maintainer-scripts\n├── 📄 missing\n├── 📄 mkdep\n├── 📄 mkinstalldirs\n├── 📄 move-if-change\n├── 📄 multilib.am\n├── 📄 symlink-tree\n├── 📄 test-driver\n├── 📄 ylwrap\n└── 📁 zlib\n\n--- Recent Commit Changes ---\n--- Commit Context Information ---\nProject Name: libstdcpp\nError Report Time: 2025-10-08\nSelected Commit SHA: 8b5d577caa32145b24acb948117f628a044028be\n------------------------------\n\ncommit 8b5d577caa32145b24acb948117f628a044028be\nAuthor: Alfie Richards <alfie.richards@arm.com>\nDate:   Wed Aug 13 20:13:28 2025 +0000\n\n    docs: Add documentation for TARGET_HAS_FMV_TARGET_ATTRIBUTE macro\n    \n    Adds documentation for the TARGET_HAS_FMV_TARGET_ATTRIBUTE macro hook.\n    \n    gcc/ChangeLog:\n    \n            * doc/tm.texi: Regenerate.\n            * doc/tm.texi.in: Add documentation for TARGET_HAS_FMV_TARGET_ATTRIBUTE.\n---\n gcc/doc/tm.texi    | 10 ++++++++++\n gcc/doc/tm.texi.in | 10 ++++++++++\n 2 files changed, 20 insertions(+)\n\ndiff --git a/gcc/doc/tm.texi b/gcc/doc/tm.texi\nindex 981bb2dca0e..0d109391f0b 100644\n--- a/gcc/doc/tm.texi\n+++ b/gcc/doc/tm.texi\n@@ -10925,6 +10925,16 @@ the function declaration to hold a pointer to a target-specific\n @code{struct cl_target_option} structure.\n @end deftypefn\n \n+@defmac TARGET_HAS_FMV_TARGET_ATTRIBUTE\n+Define this macro to zero to use @code{target_version} attributes for function\n+multiversioning (FMV) rather than @code{target} attributes.\n+\n+Targets using @code{target_version} attributes will also have\n+"target_version" FMV semantics, which allow for FMV sets defined across TU\'s\n+and using a combination of @code{target_version} and @code{target_clones}\n+attributed declarations in the definition of a FMV function set.\n+@end defmac\n+\n @defmac TARGET_CLONES_ATTR_SEPARATOR\n Define this char-typed macro to select a character that separates each\n target specific attributes from the @code{attribute(target_clones("..."))}\ndiff --git a/gcc/doc/tm.texi.in b/gcc/doc/tm.texi.in\nindex 842ea1244c8..b2851908158 100644\n--- a/gcc/doc/tm.texi.in\n+++ b/gcc/doc/tm.texi.in\n@@ -7121,6 +7121,16 @@ on this implementation detail.\n \n @hook TARGET_OPTION_VALID_VERSION_ATTRIBUTE_P\n \n+@defmac TARGET_HAS_FMV_TARGET_ATTRIBUTE\n+Define this macro to zero to use @code{target_version} attributes for function\n+multiversioning (FMV) rather than @code{target} attributes.\n+\n+Targets using @code{target_version} attributes will also have\n+"target_version" FMV semantics, which allow for FMV sets defined across TU\'s\n+and using a combination of @code{target_version} and @code{target_clones}\n+attributed declarations in the definition of a FMV function set.\n+@end defmac\n+\n @defmac TARGET_CLONES_ATTR_SEPARATOR\n Define this char-typed macro to select a character that separates each\n target specific attributes from the @code{attribute(target_clones("..."))}\n\n\n--- Fuzz Build Log (Last 500 lines) ---\nlibtool: install: (cd /out/install.d/lib/../lib64 && { ln -s -f libstdc++.so.6.0.35 libstdc++.so || { rm -f libstdc++.so && ln -s libstdc++.so.6.0.35 libstdc++.so; }; })\nlibtool: install: /usr/bin/install -c .libs/libstdc++.lai /out/install.d/lib/../lib64/libstdc++.la\nlibtool: install: /usr/bin/install -c .libs/libstdc++.a /out/install.d/lib/../lib64/libstdc++.a\nlibtool: install: chmod 644 /out/install.d/lib/../lib64/libstdc++.a\nlibtool: install: ranlib --plugin /usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/9/liblto_plugin.so  --plugin /out/build.d/./gcc/liblto_plugin.so /out/install.d/lib/../lib64/libstdc++.a\nlibtool: finish: PATH="/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/out:/sbin" ldconfig -n /out/install.d/lib/../lib64\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\nLibraries have been installed in:\n   /out/install.d/lib/../lib64\n\nIf you ever happen to want to link against installed libraries\nin a given directory, LIBDIR, you must either use libtool, and\nspecify the full pathname of the library, or use the `-LLIBDIR\'\nflag during linking and do at least one of the following:\n   - add LIBDIR to the `LD_LIBRARY_PATH\' environment variable\n     during execution\n   - add LIBDIR to the `LD_RUN_PATH\' environment variable\n     during linking\n   - use the `-Wl,-rpath -Wl,LIBDIR\' linker flag\n   - have your system administrator add LIBDIR to `/etc/ld.so.conf\'\n\nSee any operating system documentation about shared libraries for\nmore information, such as the ld(1) and ld.so(8) manual pages.\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\nmake[4]: Leaving directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/src\'\nmake[3]: Leaving directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/src\'\nmake[2]: Leaving directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/src\'\nMaking install in doc\nmake[2]: Entering directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/doc\'\nmake[3]: Entering directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/doc\'\nmake[3]: Nothing to be done for \'install-exec-am\'.\nmake[3]: Nothing to be done for \'install-data-am\'.\nmake[3]: Leaving directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/doc\'\nmake[2]: Leaving directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/doc\'\nMaking install in po\nmake[2]: Entering directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/po\'\nmake[3]: Entering directory \'/out/build.d/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu/libstdc++-v3/po\'\nmake[3]: Nothing to be done for \'install-exec-am\'.\n/bin/bash /src/libstdcpp/libstdc++-v3/../mkinstalldirs /out/install.d/share/locale\nmkdir -p -- /out/install.d/share/locale\ncatalogs=\'de.mo fr.mo\'; \\\nfor cat in $catalogs; do \\\n  cat=`basename $cat`; \\\n  lang=`echo $cat | sed \'s/\\\\.mo$//\'`; \\\n  install_dir=/out/install.d/share/locale/$lang/LC_MESSAGES; \\\n  /bin/bash'}
